Cinnamomum zeylanicum (Family Lauraceae) which is commonly known as Ceylon cinnamon or true cinnamon is an indigenous plant in Sri Lanka. Recent studies have shown many beneficial health effects of Cinnamon such as anti-hypertensive effect, anti-inflammatory properties, anti-microbial activity, blood glucose control, reducing the risk of cardiovascular disease and colonic cancer (
Mahmoodnia, Aghadavod & Rafieian-Kopaei, 2017; 
Ouattara et al., 1997; 
Khan et al., 2003; 
Shen et al., 2010).
